<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="518" pageId="2" pageNumber="517" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1498,2027]" pageId="2" pageNumber="517">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,683,1498,1523]" pageId="2" pageNumber="517">
<typeStatus box="[199,308,1498,1523]" pageId="2" pageNumber="517">Holotype</typeStatus>
description. Head and thorax.
</emphasis>
Head (
<figureCitation box="[771,879,1498,1523]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1313,1336]" captionTargetBox="[221,1337,272,1233]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1290]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Acrogonia amazonensis sp. nov. 1, body, male holotype (INPA), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 2, body, male holotype, lateral view; 3 – 9, male genitalia: 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 5, styles and connective, dorsal view; 6, apex of style at a higher magnification; 7, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 8, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 9, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 3, 9 = 1 mm; 4, 5, 7, 8 = 0.5 mm; 6 = 0. 25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437244/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="517">Figs. 1–2</figureCitation>
) strongly produced anteriorly; median length of crown approximately 9/10 interocular width and 5/10 transocular width. Crown (
<figureCitation box="[1103,1173,1534,1559]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1313,1336]" captionTargetBox="[221,1337,272,1233]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1290]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Acrogonia amazonensis sp. nov. 1, body, male holotype (INPA), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 2, body, male holotype, lateral view; 3 – 9, male genitalia: 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 5, styles and connective, dorsal view; 6, apex of style at a higher magnification; 7, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 8, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 9, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 3, 9 = 1 mm; 4, 5, 7, 8 = 0.5 mm; 6 = 0. 25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437244/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="517">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, with triangular form; with carina and elevation at transition to face; coronal suture distinct; ocelli located behind imaginary line between anterior eye angles, each approximately equidistant between median line of crown and adjacent anterior eye angle; with median fovea, without sculpturing or setae. Antennal ledges, in dorsal view, slightly protuberant; in lateral view, carinate dorsally. Frons convex; muscle impressions distinct; epistomal suture obscure medially; clypeus not produced, its contour continuing profile of frons. Thorax (
<figureCitation box="[1158,1265,1714,1739]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1313,1336]" captionTargetBox="[221,1337,272,1233]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1290]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Acrogonia amazonensis sp. nov. 1, body, male holotype (INPA), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 2, body, male holotype, lateral view; 3 – 9, male genitalia: 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 5, styles and connective, dorsal view; 6, apex of style at a higher magnification; 7, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 8, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 9, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 3, 9 = 1 mm; 4, 5, 7, 8 = 0.5 mm; 6 = 0. 25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437244/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="517">Figs. 1–2</figureCitation>
) with width of pronotum less than transocular width of head; lateral pronotal margins parallel; posterior margin emarginate; dorsopleural carinae complete; pronotal disc with rugae, without pubescence; mesonotum with scutellum not transversely striate. Forewings (
<figureCitation box="[523,632,1822,1847]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1313,1336]" captionTargetBox="[221,1337,272,1233]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1290]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Acrogonia amazonensis sp. nov. 1, body, male holotype (INPA), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 2, body, male holotype, lateral view; 3 – 9, male genitalia: 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 5, styles and connective, dorsal view; 6, apex of style at a higher magnification; 7, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 8, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 9, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 3, 9 = 1 mm; 4, 5, 7, 8 = 0.5 mm; 6 = 0. 25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437244/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="517">Figs. 1–2</figureCitation>
) with coriaceous texture; membrane restricted to apical cells, apical portions of anteapical cells and extending anteriorly along costal margin. Hind legs with femoral setal formula 2:0:0; length of first tarsomere greater than combined length of two more distal tarsomeres.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1498,2027]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,151,824]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="518" pageId="2" pageNumber="517">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,272,1930,1955]" pageId="2" pageNumber="517">Color.</emphasis>
Ground color of anterior dorsum (
<figureCitation box="[685,753,1930,1955]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1313,1336]" captionTargetBox="[221,1337,272,1233]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1290]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Acrogonia amazonensis sp. nov. 1, body, male holotype (INPA), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 2, body, male holotype, lateral view; 3 – 9, male genitalia: 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 5, styles and connective, dorsal view; 6, apex of style at a higher magnification; 7, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 8, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 9, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 3, 9 = 1 mm; 4, 5, 7, 8 = 0.5 mm; 6 = 0. 25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437244/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="517">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) mostly dark green; crown with irregular yellow maculae bordering anterior margin from apex to antennal ledges and also extending along inner eye margins; pronotum with small irregular yellow marks anteriorly; mesonotum with yellow apex. Forewings (
<figureCitation box="[1101,1208,2002,2027]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1313,1336]" captionTargetBox="[221,1337,272,1233]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1290]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Acrogonia amazonensis sp. nov. 1, body, male holotype (INPA), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 2, body, male holotype, lateral view; 3 – 9, male genitalia: 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 5, styles and connective, dorsal view; 6, apex of style at a higher magnification; 7, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 8, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 9, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 3, 9 = 1 mm; 4, 5, 7, 8 = 0.5 mm; 6 = 0. 25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437244/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="517">Figs. 1–2</figureCitation>
) dark green, except for membranous portions and irregular pale marks. Face and lateral and ventral portions of thorax yellow to greenish-yellow; frons brown on superior portion; lateral lobe of pronotum dark brown on superior portion. Legs brownish-yellow.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="518" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,824]" pageId="3" pageNumber="518">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,384,260,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="518">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[511,586,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1313,1336]" captionTargetBox="[221,1337,272,1233]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1290]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Acrogonia amazonensis sp. nov. 1, body, male holotype (INPA), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 2, body, male holotype, lateral view; 3 – 9, male genitalia: 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 5, styles and connective, dorsal view; 6, apex of style at a higher magnification; 7, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 8, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 9, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 3, 9 = 1 mm; 4, 5, 7, 8 = 0.5 mm; 6 = 0. 25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437244/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="518">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, strongly produced posteriorly; with distinct lobe on basiventral portion; dorsoapical portion folded inward; setae distributed mostly on median and distal third of disc. Subgenital plates (
<figureCitation box="[360,429,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1313,1336]" captionTargetBox="[221,1337,272,1233]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1290]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Acrogonia amazonensis sp. nov. 1, body, male holotype (INPA), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 2, body, male holotype, lateral view; 3 – 9, male genitalia: 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 5, styles and connective, dorsal view; 6, apex of style at a higher magnification; 7, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 8, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 9, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 3, 9 = 1 mm; 4, 5, 7, 8 = 0.5 mm; 6 = 0. 25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437244/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="518">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
), in ventral view, subtriangular; basal third expanded laterally and then tapering abruptly toward apex; apical portion small, digitiform, appearing articulated at its base with remainder of plate; in lateral view, plates short, not extending posteriorly beyond basal half of pygofer; plate surface with scattered setae. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[294,361,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1313,1336]" captionTargetBox="[221,1337,272,1233]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1290]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Acrogonia amazonensis sp. nov. 1, body, male holotype (INPA), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 2, body, male holotype, lateral view; 3 – 9, male genitalia: 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 5, styles and connective, dorsal view; 6, apex of style at a higher magnification; 7, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 8, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 9, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 3, 9 = 1 mm; 4, 5, 7, 8 = 0.5 mm; 6 = 0. 25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437244/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="518">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, T-shaped; stalk narrow, with median keel [a previously unknown feature in the genus], apex expanded. Style (
<figureCitation box="[490,557,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1313,1336]" captionTargetBox="[221,1337,272,1233]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1290]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Acrogonia amazonensis sp. nov. 1, body, male holotype (INPA), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 2, body, male holotype, lateral view; 3 – 9, male genitalia: 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 5, styles and connective, dorsal view; 6, apex of style at a higher magnification; 7, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 8, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 9, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 3, 9 = 1 mm; 4, 5, 7, 8 = 0.5 mm; 6 = 0. 25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437244/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="518">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, extending posteriorly slightly farther than apex of connective; preapical lobe distinct, bearing few setae; apical portion directed outward; apex acute (
<figureCitation box="[1128,1197,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1313,1336]" captionTargetBox="[221,1337,272,1233]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1290]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Acrogonia amazonensis sp. nov. 1, body, male holotype (INPA), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 2, body, male holotype, lateral view; 3 – 9, male genitalia: 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 5, styles and connective, dorsal view; 6, apex of style at a higher magnification; 7, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 8, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 9, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 3, 9 = 1 mm; 4, 5, 7, 8 = 0.5 mm; 6 = 0. 25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437244/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="518">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1313,1336]" captionTargetBox="[221,1337,272,1233]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1290]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Acrogonia amazonensis sp. nov. 1, body, male holotype (INPA), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 2, body, male holotype, lateral view; 3 – 9, male genitalia: 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 5, styles and connective, dorsal view; 6, apex of style at a higher magnification; 7, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 8, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 9, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 3, 9 = 1 mm; 4, 5, 7, 8 = 0.5 mm; 6 = 0. 25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437244/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="518">Figs. 7– 8</figureCitation>
) symmetrical; shaft, in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[578,646,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1313,1336]" captionTargetBox="[221,1337,272,1233]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1290]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Acrogonia amazonensis sp. nov. 1, body, male holotype (INPA), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 2, body, male holotype, lateral view; 3 – 9, male genitalia: 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 5, styles and connective, dorsal view; 6, apex of style at a higher magnification; 7, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 8, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 9, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 3, 9 = 1 mm; 4, 5, 7, 8 = 0.5 mm; 6 = 0. 25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437244/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="518">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
), short and slightly curved dorsally, without processes; in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[159,226,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1313,1336]" captionTargetBox="[221,1337,272,1233]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1290]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Acrogonia amazonensis sp. nov. 1, body, male holotype (INPA), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 2, body, male holotype, lateral view; 3 – 9, male genitalia: 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 5, styles and connective, dorsal view; 6, apex of style at a higher magnification; 7, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 8, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 9, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 3, 9 = 1 mm; 4, 5, 7, 8 = 0.5 mm; 6 = 0. 25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437244/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="518">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
), with pair of lateral sclerotized lines, slightly narrowed apically; aedeagal base with pair of elongate slender processes, their length twice length of shaft and apices acute. Anal tube (
<figureCitation box="[966,1034,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1313,1336]" captionTargetBox="[221,1337,272,1233]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1290]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Acrogonia amazonensis sp. nov. 1, body, male holotype (INPA), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 2, body, male holotype, lateral view; 3 – 9, male genitalia: 3, pygofer, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 5, styles and connective, dorsal view; 6, apex of style at a higher magnification; 7, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 8, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 9, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 3, 9 = 1 mm; 4, 5, 7, 8 = 0.5 mm; 6 = 0. 25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437244/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="518">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
